  <revision rev="6" vrev="1">
    <srcmd5>3e1d20f5ea11f99a12e19a54a417fd59</srcmd5>
    <version>0.4.5</version>
    <time>1783333896</time>
    <user>anag_factory</user>
    <comment>- update to 0.4.5 (bsc#1270285, CVE-2026-49825):
  * Fixed a security vulnerability where javascript: URLs in
    xlink:href attributes were not sanitized
    when``safe_attrs_only=False``, allowing cross-site scripting
    (XSS) attacks. The fix requires lxml&gt;=6.1.1, which adds
    xlink:href to the set of link attributes iterated by
    rewrite_links(). Reported by Guillem Lefait (@glefait).</comment>
    <requestid>1363833</requestid>
  </revision>
